From: Xiubo Li <xiubli@redhat.com>
Date: Wed, 2 Mar 2022 14:51:53 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] ceph: fix inode reference leakage in ceph_get_snapdir()
Git-commit: 322794d3355c33adcc4feace0045d85a8e4ed813
Patch-mainline: v5.18-rc1
References: CVE-2022-49109 bsc#1237836

[ discard_new_inode not available, but equivalent to unlock_new_inode + iput ]

The ceph_get_inode() will search for or insert a new inode into the
hash for the given vino, and return a reference to it. If new is
non-NULL, its reference is consumed.

We should release the reference when in error handing cases.

Signed-off-by: Xiubo Li <xiubli@redhat.com>
Reviewed-by: Jeff Layton <jlayton@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Ilya Dryomov <idryomov@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 fs/ceph/inode.c |   12 ++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/fs/ceph/inode.c
+++ b/fs/ceph/inode.c
@@ -85,13 +85,13 @@ struct inode *ceph_get_snapdir(struct in
 	if (!S_ISDIR(parent->i_mode)) {
 		pr_warn_once("bad snapdir parent type (mode=0%o)\n",
 			     parent->i_mode);
-		return ERR_PTR(-ENOTDIR);
+		goto err;
 	}
 
 	if (!(inode->i_state & I_NEW) && !S_ISDIR(inode->i_mode)) {
 		pr_warn_once("bad snapdir inode type (mode=0%o)\n",
 			     inode->i_mode);
-		return ERR_PTR(-ENOTDIR);
+		goto err;
 	}
 
 	inode->i_mode = parent->i_mode;
@@ -102,6 +102,14 @@ struct inode *ceph_get_snapdir(struct in
 	ci->i_snap_caps = CEPH_CAP_PIN; /* so we can open */
 	ci->i_rbytes = 0;
 	return inode;
+err:
+	if ((inode->i_state & I_NEW)) {
+		/* discard_new_inode(inode); */
+		unlock_new_inode(inode);
+		iput(inode);
+	} else
+		iput(inode);
+	return ERR_PTR(-ENOTDIR);
 }
 
 const struct inode_operations ceph_file_iops = {
